</p></section><section id="M155104-B84" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph ">Answer</ph></title><table id="M155103-TB85" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="stage" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="60*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Classification 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Print Quality</b> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> general</b> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In release 4.2.0.0 the height positioning of the beam of the left, right or both was not always executed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This is machine dependent. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The incorrect height has impact on the execution of calibrations and eventually the print quality.
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Service</b>
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Installation</b> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In release 4.2.0.0 the height positioning of the beam of the left, right or both was not always executed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This is machine dependent. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The incorrect height can let the execution of calibrations fail.
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> SDS tests</b> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In release 4.2.0.0 the following tests can fail due to height positioning error of the beam: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">03-6-018 Go to highest Z motion system height, 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">03-6-019 Find Z motion system home position, 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">03-6-020 Check Z motion system range [Special Tests] 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">03-6-021 Check carriage height positions [Special Tests]
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-43B0B0A9-D1D1-44BB-BF1A-AAF3076E205E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>R4.2.1.0</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
